title: Distracted Boyfriend
description: A stock photo of a man turning to look at another woman while his girlfriend looks on in disbelief, used to represent shifting attention or priorities.

title: Expanding Brain
description: A series of images showing increasingly illuminated brains to represent ascending levels of intellect or enlightenment.

title: First World Problems
description: An attractive person crying over trivial inconveniences, satirizing privileged complaints.

title: Change My Mind
description: Steven Crowder seated at a table with a sign inviting others to change his mind, parodied by swapping the sign’s text.

title: Woman Yelling at a Cat
description: A split image of a Reality TV star yelling and a confused cat at a dinner table, used to depict arguments or misunderstandings.

title: Mocking SpongeBob
description: SpongeBob bent over in a chicken-like pose, captioned with alternating uppercase and lowercase letters to mock a statement.

title: Grumpy Cat
description: A cat with a perpetually displeased expression, symbolizing disdain or negativity.

title: Overly Attached Girlfriend
description: A woman with wide eyes and a creepy smile, captioned with clingy or obsessive statements to parody relationship insecurity.

title: Scumbag Steve
description: A teenager wearing a sideways cap and fur-lined jacket, used to represent selfish or unethical behavior.

title: Bad Luck Brian
description: A school-photo boy with braces and a plaid sweater-vest, paired with captions of unfortunate events.

title: Success Kid
description: A toddler clenching a fistful of sand with a determined expression, representing small victories.

title: Ancient Aliens
description: Giorgio Tsoukalos gesturing wildly on the History Channel, captioned to blame everything on aliens.

title: Philosoraptor
description: A velociraptor pondering with its claw on its chin, used for philosophical or paradoxical questions.

title: Y U No
description: A crudely drawn face screaming “Y U NO…” to express frustration at someone’s actions.

title: Italian Brainrot Animals
description: AI-generated bizarre Italian creatures with humorous backstories, exemplifying modern surreal ‘brainrot’ humor.

title: Skibidi Toilet
description: A surreal meme of a human head emerging from a toilet, often set to chaotic music for absurdist effect.

title: Gyatt
description: Slang praising someone’s physique, especially curvy figures, popularized on TikTok.

title: Rizz
description: Short for ‘charisma,’ used to denote someone’s charm or attractiveness in social contexts.

title: Among Us (‘sus’)
description: From the multiplayer game Among Us, ‘sus’ denotes suspicion; used broadly to call out untrustworthy behavior.

title: Doge
description: A Shiba Inu dog surrounded by multicolored Comic Sans text in broken English to convey inner monologue.
